******************************************
******       BETARUN CHANGES         *****
****** Latest changes at top of file *****
******************************************

PA: 5/4/2001: Changed locallab generation in linux runtime system
    generator: .L76 is better than L76, since it is stripped
    from runtime system by assembler, and thus does not appear in 
    disassemblies when debugging.

PA: 30/3/2001:
    Larger movement of code from valhallaFindComp.c and outpattern.c
    to GC/xxx_stack.c (stack specific stuff).
    Added find_activation in GC/stack.c. Used by dynamic exceptions.
    Removed valhallaFindComp.{c,h}
    Removed a number of old files that had resurrected. 
    Probably due to bad cvs join.

PA: 14/03/2001:
    Rewrite of CallbackEntry visitor in cbfa.c:
    Old one skipped visit of first entry in all CBFA blocks but the
    first.
    Could be cause of spurious callback releated bugs.

HML: 22/02/2001:

   Callback fix. GPR11 is used instead of GPR24 in callback stub. Must
   Be used together with similar fix in compiler (rcm 824).
   
   m NEWRUN/Callback.c
   


